String word = "hello_world"; String[] strArr = word.split("_"); strArr ==> {"hello" , "world"}

String word = "helloworld"; String[] strArr = word.split("o"); strArr ==> {"hell", "w", "rld"}

String word = "java is fun"; String[] strArr = word.split(" "); strArr ==> {"java" , "is", "fun"}

String word = "https://learn.cybertekschool.com/courses/130";

String[] strArr = word.split("/"); strArr ==> {"https:","","learn.cybertekschool.com","courses","130"};

String word = "java program";

String[] strArr = word.split("a"); strArr ==> {"j","v", " progr", "m"};

How many 'a's in word? strArr.length - 1 (3) will give us number of a letters.

The above is good when word does not start or end with a.
